1
00:00:05,881 --> 00:00:08,926
<i>["Headhunt" by Okamoto's]</i>

2
00:00:08,926 --> 00:00:11,970
[man singing in Japanese]

3
00:00:11,970 --> 00:00:19,019
<i>♪ ♪</i>

4
00:01:02,145 --> 00:01:04,273
CELTY: You'll never
straighten this mess out.

5
00:01:04,273 --> 00:01:06,567
Your best bet is to run for it.

6
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:08,026
MAN: Ah, come on!

7
00:01:08,026 --> 00:01:09,903
Don't run!
Asshole!

8
00:01:09,903 --> 00:01:11,822
‐ I only came to this town
to get some payback

9
00:01:11,822 --> 00:01:13,031
for the fight
that you guys started.

10
00:01:13,031 --> 00:01:14,324
KINE: Sorry, Celty.

11
00:01:14,324 --> 00:01:16,785
Would you mind taking Ms. Akane
somewhere safe?

12
00:01:16,785 --> 00:01:18,245
CELTY:
Don't let me down, Shooter.

13
00:01:18,245 --> 00:01:19,788
[Cóiste‐Bodhar neighs]

14
00:01:24,376 --> 00:01:31,383
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15
00:01:55,991 --> 00:01:58,076
[Cóiste‐Bodhar neighs]

16
00:01:58,076 --> 00:02:00,203
ALL: Huh?

17
00:02:00,203 --> 00:02:01,538
BOTH: Whoa.

18
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:08,295
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19
00:02:13,467 --> 00:02:15,260
[Akane gasps]

20
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:16,678
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21
00:02:16,678 --> 00:02:18,263
[Cóiste‐Bodhar neighs]

22
00:02:21,099 --> 00:02:22,976
AKANE:
It all began with a cell phone.

23
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:32,110
<i>[uncertain chamber music]</i>

24
00:02:32,110 --> 00:02:33,570
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:35,822
AKANE: I'm not sure,
but I think my family

26
00:02:35,822 --> 00:02:38,492
was probably more well‐off
than others.

27
00:02:38,492 --> 00:02:40,911
People have always said to me,

28
00:02:40,911 --> 00:02:43,955
"You've never wanted
for a thing, have you?"

29
00:02:43,955 --> 00:02:46,833
My father, my mother,
and my grandfather

30
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:49,378
were always super nice to me.

31
00:02:49,378 --> 00:02:50,712
They gave me a cell phone

32
00:02:50,712 --> 00:02:53,048
because they thought
it would keep me safe.

33
00:02:53,048 --> 00:02:57,302
My father said I was
still too young for it, though.

34
00:02:57,302 --> 00:02:58,303
BOY: Wow!

35
00:02:58,303 --> 00:03:00,889
[all laugh]

36
00:03:00,889 --> 00:03:04,559
AKANE: I never went
on the Internet at first.

37
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:07,813
But then,
right around that time...

38
00:03:07,813 --> 00:03:11,108
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39
00:03:11,108 --> 00:03:12,317
Huh?

40
00:03:12,317 --> 00:03:13,568
[girls snickering]

41
00:03:13,568 --> 00:03:15,612
I saw someone get bullied.

42
00:03:17,739 --> 00:03:22,160
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,829
Stop bullying her.

44
00:03:23,829 --> 00:03:25,705
I just said it.

45
00:03:25,705 --> 00:03:27,207
ALL: Uh...

46
00:03:27,207 --> 00:03:28,917
BOYS: Huh?

47
00:03:28,917 --> 00:03:31,336
AKANE: Yeah, I was scared.

48
00:03:31,336 --> 00:03:32,963
I thought for sure
that I was the one

49
00:03:32,963 --> 00:03:35,674
who was gonna
get picked on next.

50
00:03:35,674 --> 00:03:36,967
But...

51
00:03:37,968 --> 00:03:40,178
Nothing happened.

52
00:03:40,178 --> 00:03:42,389
The bullying stopped,

53
00:03:42,389 --> 00:03:44,349
and I didn't get bullied either.

54
00:03:44,349 --> 00:03:46,852
Everyone understood
it was wrong...

55
00:03:46,852 --> 00:03:49,771
At least, that's what I thought
at the time.

56
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:52,357
My friends and I
were always smiling.

57
00:03:52,357 --> 00:03:54,734
I lived the greatest life ever,

58
00:03:54,734 --> 00:03:57,362
and so I decided
I wanted to do more

59
00:03:57,362 --> 00:03:59,448
to make other people smile.

60
00:03:59,448 --> 00:04:01,825
While I was growing up,
I always believed

61
00:04:01,825 --> 00:04:04,369
that my dad was in the business
of selling art,

62
00:04:04,369 --> 00:04:06,746
so I thought
I'd become an artist.

63
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:08,832
I could create
beautiful paintings

64
00:04:08,832 --> 00:04:10,667
that would make everyone smile,

65
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:12,544
and my father could sell them.

66
00:04:12,544 --> 00:04:14,546
Oh. Sorry.

67
00:04:14,546 --> 00:04:17,048
I was talking about
my cell phone.

68
00:04:17,048 --> 00:04:19,593
It wasn't long
after the bullying incident

69
00:04:19,593 --> 00:04:22,220
that I left my phone
at a friend's house.

70
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:23,764
GIRL: You don't
have to remind me, Mom.

71
00:04:23,764 --> 00:04:26,057
I only do
what Akane tells me to do.

72
00:04:26,057 --> 00:04:27,934
WOMAN: And what about
her other classmates?

73
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:30,562
They don't do anything
to displease her, do they?

74
00:04:30,562 --> 00:04:32,606
GIRL: No!
WOMAN: The Awakusus

75
00:04:32,606 --> 00:04:35,275
are really frightening people,
you understand?

76
00:04:35,275 --> 00:04:37,068
If you had a fight
and injured her,

77
00:04:37,068 --> 00:04:41,239
that would give them an excuse
to make trouble for us.

78
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:44,326
AKANE: My friend's mother
and father came over right away

79
00:04:44,326 --> 00:04:45,660
to return my cell phone.

80
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:47,412
AKANE'S MOTHER:
That's very considerate.

81
00:04:47,412 --> 00:04:48,914
AKANE:
And that's what made me think

82
00:04:48,914 --> 00:04:50,081
something was wrong.

83
00:04:50,081 --> 00:04:51,750
I mean, I would have seen her

84
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:53,001
at school the next day.

85
00:04:53,001 --> 00:04:56,379
There was no need
to bring it themselves.

86
00:04:56,379 --> 00:04:58,924
Uh...let's see.

87
00:05:09,017 --> 00:05:11,102
And that's when I found out

88
00:05:11,102 --> 00:05:14,064
what our family business
really is.

89
00:05:14,064 --> 00:05:18,401
GIRL: Everyone was saying,
"Let's bully Akane next."

90
00:05:18,401 --> 00:05:20,278
I told 'em I didn't want to,

91
00:05:20,278 --> 00:05:22,614
but they told me
if I bullied you with them,

92
00:05:22,614 --> 00:05:24,449
then they'd stop bullying me,

93
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:27,077
but then one of the girls‐‐

94
00:05:27,077 --> 00:05:29,204
she said that your father
was really scary,

95
00:05:29,204 --> 00:05:31,832
so we shouldn't make you mad.

96
00:05:31,832 --> 00:05:33,416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

97
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:36,586
AKANE:
Everybody was afraid of me.

98
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:38,505
All my friends at school,

99
00:05:38,505 --> 00:05:39,881
their families,

100
00:05:39,881 --> 00:05:41,132
everyone‐‐

101
00:05:41,132 --> 00:05:42,968
it was all just a lie.

102
00:05:42,968 --> 00:05:47,055
They were each
just pretending to be happy.

103
00:05:47,055 --> 00:05:49,766
AKANE'S MOTHER:
Akane? Dinnertime!

104
00:05:49,766 --> 00:05:52,352
AKANE:
I went and had dinner as usual.

105
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:55,188
It was just my mom and me
that day.

106
00:05:55,188 --> 00:05:57,816
I don't remember what we
talked about while we ate‐‐

107
00:05:57,816 --> 00:05:59,734
probably the usual stuff,

108
00:05:59,734 --> 00:06:01,403
like what happened at school.

109
00:06:01,403 --> 00:06:04,489
What? Hmm.

110
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:07,284
I'm not sure,
but I thought I should just act

111
00:06:07,284 --> 00:06:09,452
like nothing had happened,

112
00:06:09,452 --> 00:06:10,704
but...

113
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:17,210
[cries]

114
00:06:34,978 --> 00:06:37,022
[knocking]
AKANE'S MOTHER: Akane!

115
00:06:37,022 --> 00:06:38,106
What's wrong?

116
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:39,733
Honey, open the door.

117
00:06:39,733 --> 00:06:42,694
AKANE: My mother and father
figured out right away

118
00:06:42,694 --> 00:06:47,198
that I'd discovered what
our family's business really is.

119
00:06:47,198 --> 00:06:49,034
<i>♪ ♪</i>

120
00:06:49,034 --> 00:06:50,910
Thank you for dinner.

121
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:53,204
<i>♪ ♪</i>

122
00:06:53,204 --> 00:06:54,998
‐ [sighs]

123
00:06:54,998 --> 00:06:56,207
<i>♪ ♪</i>

124
00:06:56,207 --> 00:06:57,709
[door handle turns]
[Akane gasps]

125
00:06:57,709 --> 00:07:00,003
<i>♪ ♪</i>

126
00:07:00,003 --> 00:07:01,504
‐ Huh?

127
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:08,553
AKANE:
I couldn't look at him anymore.

128
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:11,348
So I thought
if I went someplace

129
00:07:11,348 --> 00:07:14,392
where nobody knew me
or the Awakusu name,

130
00:07:14,392 --> 00:07:17,604
then, somehow,
something might change.

131
00:07:17,604 --> 00:07:21,024
And then,
on this message board...

132
00:07:23,068 --> 00:07:26,529
I ended up learning a lot
from that person,

133
00:07:26,529 --> 00:07:30,533
even though
it scared me a little bit.

134
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:34,996
<i>♪ ♪</i>

135
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:36,373
[gasps]

136
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:38,708
NAKURA: Hello, there.

137
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:40,669
You're Akane, right?

138
00:07:40,669 --> 00:07:42,170
Nice to meet you.

139
00:07:42,170 --> 00:07:44,255
I'm Nakura.

140
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:46,257
AKANE:
And then, one day, I met her.

141
00:07:46,257 --> 00:07:48,927
She was a nice, pretty lady,

142
00:07:48,927 --> 00:07:51,262
and she seemed super smart too,

143
00:07:51,262 --> 00:07:53,056
so I opened up to her

144
00:07:53,056 --> 00:07:55,558
and told her my whole story.

145
00:07:55,558 --> 00:07:59,020
<i>♪ ♪</i>

146
00:07:59,020 --> 00:08:00,146
Hmm?

147
00:08:00,146 --> 00:08:02,357
NAKURA:
Oh, this person is Izaya.

148
00:08:02,357 --> 00:08:04,442
Don't worry‐‐
he's a friend of mine,

149
00:08:04,442 --> 00:08:06,027
and he can help you out.

150
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:07,278
‐ Uh‐huh.

151
00:08:07,278 --> 00:08:09,614
She introduced me to Izaya.

152
00:08:09,614 --> 00:08:14,119
Before I knew it, I had told
them everything about my family.

153
00:08:14,119 --> 00:08:16,162
Maybe it was too much.

154
00:08:16,162 --> 00:08:19,457
Maybe they'd be scared of me,
now that they knew,

155
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:20,875
but...
[gasps]

156
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:23,795
Izaya was nice enough
to tell me,

157
00:08:23,795 --> 00:08:25,296
"It's quite all right.

158
00:08:25,296 --> 00:08:27,340
"I'm a little scared,
to be honest with you,

159
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:32,137
but you're not
your family's business, Akane."

160
00:08:32,137 --> 00:08:36,433
One month later,
I ran away from home.

161
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:39,978
I spent the night
at manga cafés and diners.

162
00:08:39,978 --> 00:08:42,147
He gave me
lots of good pointers‐‐

163
00:08:42,147 --> 00:08:44,858
tips on how to live
as a runaway.

164
00:08:44,858 --> 00:08:47,360
I remember him asking me once,

165
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,988
"Do you hate
your grandfather and your dad?"

166
00:08:49,988 --> 00:08:53,199
"I don't know"
was how I answered.

167
00:08:53,199 --> 00:08:57,203
Then he told me that I should
think it over carefully

168
00:08:57,203 --> 00:08:59,664
until I did know,
and then he said,

169
00:08:59,664 --> 00:09:03,460
"There's no guarantee they'll
be safe in the meantime."

170
00:09:03,460 --> 00:09:04,627
[gasps]

171
00:09:04,627 --> 00:09:05,837
He told me he was worried

172
00:09:05,837 --> 00:09:07,505
because
both my grandfather and dad

173
00:09:07,505 --> 00:09:09,507
had made a lot of enemies.

174
00:09:09,507 --> 00:09:12,177
Then he said to me,
"The person in this photo

175
00:09:12,177 --> 00:09:15,472
"is the scariest hitman
in all of Ikebukuro,

176
00:09:15,472 --> 00:09:17,265
"and he might be
targeting your family

177
00:09:17,265 --> 00:09:19,851
even as we're sitting here."

178
00:09:19,851 --> 00:09:22,353
Then he told me the man's name.

179
00:09:22,353 --> 00:09:24,856
He said it was Shizuo Heiwajima.

180
00:09:24,856 --> 00:09:28,026
[camera shutters snapping]

181
00:09:28,026 --> 00:09:29,444
<i>♪ ♪</i>

182
00:09:29,444 --> 00:09:31,029
CELTY: If we go on like this,

183
00:09:31,029 --> 00:09:33,448
we'll attract
too much attention.

184
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:44,042
[tires screeching]

185
00:09:44,042 --> 00:09:46,336
[engine revving]

186
00:09:47,545 --> 00:09:50,215
[cell phone chirping]

187
00:09:50,215 --> 00:09:52,842
‐ Pain in the ass!

188
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:56,096
SHINRA: So, your men
were taken out by Shizuo, huh?

189
00:09:57,055 --> 00:09:58,389
But I do wonder what he's doing

190
00:09:58,389 --> 00:10:00,058
hanging out with Akane.

191
00:10:00,058 --> 00:10:03,311
‐ Yeah. That's exactly
what we'd like to know.

192
00:10:03,311 --> 00:10:04,729
‐ Listen.

193
00:10:04,729 --> 00:10:07,023
What sort of shape
were your men's bodies in?

194
00:10:07,023 --> 00:10:08,733
My interests are personal.

195
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:10,985
Nothing more than that.
I promise.

196
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:15,448
‐ Hmm.

197
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:21,037
Well, this definitely
is not Shizuo's handiwork.

198
00:10:21,037 --> 00:10:22,747
SHIKI: Is that your opinion
as a doctor?

199
00:10:22,747 --> 00:10:25,875
‐ No, that opinion's
as a lifelong friend.

200
00:10:25,875 --> 00:10:28,002
These bodies look far too good.

201
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:30,839
Shizuo wouldn't
have stopped there.

202
00:10:30,839 --> 00:10:32,257
‐ Hmm.

203
00:10:32,257 --> 00:10:33,633
‐ But then again,

204
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,760
I think you know this already,
don't you?

205
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:37,387
‐ Yeah, maybe I do.

206
00:10:37,387 --> 00:10:39,556
But who else out there
can kill our guys

207
00:10:39,556 --> 00:10:41,850
with only his bare hands?

208
00:10:44,102 --> 00:10:45,353
Hmm?

209
00:10:53,695 --> 00:10:56,239
[birds singing]

210
00:10:59,284 --> 00:11:00,410
[cell phone chirping]

211
00:11:00,410 --> 00:11:02,120
‐ [laughs]
Mm.

212
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:03,454
Hey. It's you.

213
00:11:03,454 --> 00:11:04,664
What's up?

214
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:05,874
I thought you and I had finished

215
00:11:05,874 --> 00:11:07,876
our conversation this morning.

216
00:11:07,876 --> 00:11:10,628
Or maybe you just miss
the sound of my voice.

217
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:14,632
If so, that's a bigger
commitment than I'm ready for.

218
00:11:14,632 --> 00:11:16,134
[branches crashing]

219
00:11:16,134 --> 00:11:17,969
‐ Look, I don't have time
for you to babble on

220
00:11:17,969 --> 00:11:20,138
with your lame jokes.

221
00:11:20,138 --> 00:11:21,431
What'd you say to Mikado?

222
00:11:21,431 --> 00:11:22,974
IZAYA:
What are you talking about?

223
00:11:22,974 --> 00:11:24,517
‐ Someone jacked my chat name,

224
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:26,436
and I'm pretty sure it was you.

225
00:11:26,436 --> 00:11:27,854
‐ And your proof?

226
00:11:27,854 --> 00:11:30,106
MASAOMI: Only you
would do something like that.

227
00:11:30,106 --> 00:11:32,192
So? What'd you say to him?

228
00:11:32,192 --> 00:11:33,484
‐ Hold on.

229
00:11:33,484 --> 00:11:36,487
Why do you think
that I said anything to Mikado?

230
00:11:36,487 --> 00:11:38,531
Even if I did assume your name,

231
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:42,368
it doesn't necessarily mean
that I talked to Taro Tanaka.

232
00:11:42,368 --> 00:11:45,538
‐ If someone named Izaya Orihara
breaks into my account

233
00:11:45,538 --> 00:11:47,749
just to go and steal
my chat name,

234
00:11:47,749 --> 00:11:50,501
what the hell else would he want
to use the name for?

235
00:11:50,501 --> 00:11:53,213
‐ If you're right,
what would you do about it?

236
00:11:53,213 --> 00:11:54,839
MASAOMI: Answer the question!

237
00:11:54,839 --> 00:11:58,009
‐ You may not have time
to chat with me.

238
00:11:58,009 --> 00:11:59,844
Don't you know
that something's happening

239
00:11:59,844 --> 00:12:01,679
in Ikebukuro right now?

240
00:12:01,679 --> 00:12:03,556
‐ What are you talking about?

241
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:06,184
‐ The person you should be
asking this to

242
00:12:06,184 --> 00:12:07,685
is Mikado himself.

243
00:12:07,685 --> 00:12:10,063
Just go straight up to him,
and say,

244
00:12:10,063 --> 00:12:14,525
"That wasn't me yesterday.
It was Izaya Orihara."

245
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:15,860
Easy enough, right?

246
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:18,988
Since you and Mikado
are besties and all.

247
00:12:18,988 --> 00:12:20,406
MASAOMI: Shut it.

248
00:12:20,406 --> 00:12:22,242
‐ No matter what you do,

249
00:12:22,242 --> 00:12:25,161
it seems that's how
Mikado is gonna see you.

250
00:12:25,161 --> 00:12:26,204
It's bad.

251
00:12:26,204 --> 00:12:28,581
That boy is way too trusting.

252
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:30,041
He's beyond hope,

253
00:12:30,041 --> 00:12:32,293
and that's why
he's such a noble choice,

254
00:12:32,293 --> 00:12:33,628
like a sacrificial lamb.

255
00:12:33,628 --> 00:12:34,796
‐ I said shut it, you‐‐

256
00:12:37,090 --> 00:12:41,010
‐ I really dislike
being yelled at.

257
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:42,762
[Chikage chuckles]

258
00:12:42,762 --> 00:12:45,181
‐ Bastard.

259
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:47,141
